@page "/"

<PageTitle>RNA Therapy Platform</PageTitle>

<div class="home">
    <div class="hero">
        <h2>RNA Therapy Platform</h2>
        <p>
            Browse RNA therapies, assess biomarkers, synthesize mRNA, and control lab equipment
            — all from your browser. 100% client-side, no data leaves your device.
        </p>
        <p class="help-block">
            This platform runs entirely in your browser using WebAssembly. No server processes your data.
            All scoring algorithms, therapy logic, and protocol steps execute locally.
            The only network connections are WebSocket (wss://) links to ESP32 lab controllers for real-time equipment control.
            Total hardware cost: ~$250 (4x ESP32 + sensors + motors). Total reagent cost: ~$1,600. Combined: ~$2,000 for a complete mRNA synthesis lab.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-features">
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>10 RNA Therapies</strong>
                <span>Rejuvenation, cold, flu, COVID, cancer, wound healing, hair, muscle, allergy</span>
                <div class="help">Each therapy has: mechanism of action, mRNA construct details (gene, length, Addgene/GenBank source), LNP lipid nanoparticle formulation, dosing protocol, delivery method with full administration instructions, clinical trial status, and real scoring logic that computes eligibility from your inputs.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>Biological Age Assessment</strong>
                <span>6-pillar scoring: PhenoAge, piRNA, miRNA, senescence, pathways, telomere</span>
                <div class="help">Levine PhenoAge algorithm (2018) uses exact published coefficients from NHANES III to compute biological age from 9 blood biomarkers (albumin, ALP, creatinine, CRP, glucose, WBC, lymphocyte%, MCV, RDW). Optional: Duke 2026 piRNA panel (6 piRNAs, 86% 2-year survival prediction), miRNA aging signatures (miR-34a, miR-21, miR-155), SASP senescence markers (p16, GDF15, IL-6, TNF-a), NAD+/SIRT/AMPK pathway health, and telomere length.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>mRNA Construct Library</strong>
                <span>Gene sequences, sources (Addgene, GenBank), LNP formulations, dosing</span>
                <div class="help">Each construct lists the gene name, nucleotide length, biological function, and where to buy the DNA template. Sources include Addgene (nonprofit plasmid repository, ~$75/plasmid) and GenBank accession numbers. LNP formulations specify exact lipid molar ratios for each delivery route (IM, IV, intranasal, topical, microneedle, SC).</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>ESP32 Lab Control</strong>
                <span>WSS-connected heat block, syringe pumps, UV spectro, centrifuge, gel</span>
                <div class="help">4 ESP32-S3 microcontrollers ($4 each) connected via WebSocket. #1 Controller: PID heat block (37°C for IVT), UV spectrophotometer (A260/A280 for RNA purity), brushless centrifuge (8000 RPM purification), gel electrophoresis (100V, size verification). #2 Stepper: dedicated syringe pump timing for precise 3:1 LNP mixing. #3 Environment: pH meter, magnetic stirrer, vortex, UV-C sterilizer, fume hood, emergency stop, gas detector, freezer/fridge monitoring. #4 QC: gel camera imaging, DLS particle sizer (Stokes-Einstein, target 60-100nm), turbidity sensor.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>12-Step IVT Protocol</strong>
                <span>Template prep through LNP encapsulation — guided step by step</span>
                <div class="help">In Vitro Transcription protocol customized per therapy. Steps: (1) linearize plasmid template, (2) purify template DNA, (3) QC template concentration via UV spectro, (4) T7 IVT with CleanCap + m1-pseudouridine, (5) DNase treatment, (6) purify mRNA, (7) QC yield A260/A280, (8) gel electrophoresis size check, (9) LNP microfluidic encapsulation via syringe pumps, (10) buffer exchange/dialysis, (11) final QC, (12) storage at -80°C. Each step shows temperature, duration, equipment, and detailed notes.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <strong>PASS / FAIL Verdict</strong>
                <span>Rejuvenation eligibility: OSK, OSKM, SB000 protocol assessment</span>
                <div class="help">For rejuvenation therapy: composite score from 6 pillars, each weighted and scored 0-100. PASS requires composite >= 60 AND no single pillar below 30 AND senescence burden not critical. Evaluates 3 protocols: OSK (Oct4/Sox2/Klf4 — safest, no c-Myc oncogene), OSKM (+ c-Myc — most potent, tumor risk), SB000 (novel single-factor, comparable potency, minimal identity disruption). For other therapies: eligibility computed from patient-specific inputs (timing, severity, lab results).</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:1rem;">
            <a href="therapy/common-cold" class="btn-primary">Browse Therapies</a>
            <div class="help">Opens the therapy catalog showing all 10 RNA therapies. Click any therapy to expand details: mechanism, constructs, formulation, dosing, references. Each has an "Assess & Dose" button to enter patient data and compute eligibility.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
            <a href="assess/biological-age" class="btn-secondary">Age Assessment</a>
            <div class="help">Opens the 6-pillar biological age assessment. Enter 9 required blood biomarkers (standard lab panel) plus optional RNA/senescence/pathway/telomere panels. Computes PhenoAge biological age, composite score, and rejuvenation protocol eligibility. Includes sample data presets for healthy and unhealthy profiles.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
            <a href="lab/dashboard" class="btn-secondary">Lab Dashboard</a>
            <div class="help">Opens the ESP32 #1 lab controller dashboard. Enter the WebSocket URL (wss://ESP32_IP:9123) to connect. Shows real-time equipment status with live updates every 500ms. Controls: heat block target temperature + PID, syringe pump flow rates + volumes, UV spectro measurement trigger, centrifuge RPM + duration, gel voltage + duration.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="science-summary">
        <h3>Therapy Categories</h3>
        <p class="section-help">Therapies are grouped by medical application. Each category contains therapies at different clinical stages — from Research (lab studies only) through Preclinical (animal testing), Clinical (human trials Phase 1-3), to Approved (FDA-authorized, e.g. COVID vaccines).</p>
        <div class="hero-features">
            @foreach (var group in TherapyCatalog.All.GroupBy(t => t.Category))
            {
                <div class="feature">
                    <strong>@group.Key</strong>
                    <span>@string.Join(", ", group.Select(t => t.Name))</span>
                </div>
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
